	<p><%= application.name %> is not just a great file sharing and collaboration platform.  It can be configured to be optimized for other applications as well.  For example, if you're into music, you can configure the default desktop application to be a media player rather than the file browser. You can configure <%= application.name %> to suit your needs. </p>

	<div class="attention"><div class="emphasis"><%= application.name %> is a Cloud Based Operating System!</div></div>

	<h2>It's an Operating System</h2>
	<p><%= application.name %> is also a cloud based operating system.  This means that you can create new custom applications on top of the platform.  When you build a new desktop application, you build on top of an operating system that includes support for things like the file system, window management, and account management. Modern web applications have the same needs. <%= application.name %> is a platform for building modern complex web applications in a much easier, faster, and more cohesive way. </p>

